          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was pressed in the form of a rectangular",
                "tablet (15x4x1 mm3) of scandium oxide. In the",
                "scandium fraction, separated after the irradiation,",
                "no isotopes with mass numbers > 44 have been found.",
                "Those isotopes would be inevitably produced in the",
                "presence of heavy target contaminants."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "CHSEP",
                "INTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Targets were irradiated in the",
                "internal proton beam of the Joint Nuclear Research",
                "Institute synchrocyclotron during 15-20 min. The",
                "thickness of the target along the beam was ~ 1 mm.",
                "The variation of the incident proton energy was",
                "achieved by suitable choice of target radius. The",
                "determination of the proton beam intensity was made",
                "by the yield of the reaction A127(p,3pn) Na24. The",
                "major mass of the irradiated target was dissolved in",
                "the concentrated hydrochloric acid saturated with",
                "gaseous HC1, 15 mg of the titanium carrier being",
                "present."
              ]
            }
          ],
